# Documentation Updates

**Update documentation whenever the app changes.** Documentation must stay in sync with the codebase.

## What to Update

| Change Type | Files to Update |
|-------------|-----------------|
| New feature, API, or UI | `README.md`, `CHANGELOG.md` (add to [Unreleased]), `backend/README.md` if API changed |
| New entity/table | `README.md`, `backend/README.md`, `.cursor/rules/bperp-database-schema.mdc`, `context files/INTERNAL-ROADMAP.md` if import-related |
| New route or endpoint | `README.md` (API Endpoints table), `backend/README.md` (API Overview) |
| Architecture or deployment change | `README.md`, `context files/INTERNAL-ROADMAP.md`, `docs/` as needed |
| Cursor / AI rule change | Relevant `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` |

## Workflow

1. Make code changes
2. Update relevant documentation in the same session
3. Add CHANGELOG entry for user-facing or significant changes
4. Verify README and backend README reflect current API and features

## Before Committing

- [ ] Documentation updated (README, CHANGELOG, backend README, `.cursor/rules` as needed)
